bioghist.p:
Culpepper family members include John Luther Culpepper (1821-1884), Henry C. Culpepper’s grandfather, was an attorney, state legislator, agriculturalist, and solider, and he settled in Tarboro, N.C., where he had a successful law and planting career; John Luther Culpepper, Jr. (1850-1932), Henry C. Culpepper’s father, was an attorney, farmer, guardsman, and author, and he wrote a history of Edgecombe Country, but his true loves were hunting and plating; 
                Henry C. Culpepper, Jr. (1913?-1981), Henry C. Culpepper’s son, served for 30 years as an aviator in the United States Navy and he was stationed in the South Pacific and won the Legion of Merit during the World War II; Ann Preston Culpepper (1891-1967), Henry C. Culpepper’s cousin, was a teacher, actress, writer, and civic leader; 
                Penelope Culpepper Hayes (1946-), Henry C. Culpepper’s granddaughter, was a writer and she discovered all these materials in the attic and donated them to the Random University Archives and Special Collections Department in January 2015.
